summary: (Part 3) 4: "I found it more interesting seeing Imane pushing Sofiane away and accepting (maybe encouraging even, so she could...
question: (Part 3) 4: "I found it more interesting seeing Imane pushing Sofiane away and accepting (maybe encouraging even, so she could move on too) his relationship with Manon"...excuse me, what? Is it just me or that never happened in the show? She was jealous the whole time and did her best to break them up. She went as far as bringing back Manon's toxic ex-boyfriend (worse idea ever, that was cruel and turned her into a villain in her own season).
answer:
“(Part 4) 5: The fact that those choices made more sense to them is the biggest problem. And there are at least 10 more problems with this season (like the Idriss/Eliott subplot, the villainization of Le Crew, Manon and Charles subplot, too many apologies from Imane and not enough to Imane, the lack of Sofimane developpment, etc.). In french, that answer is what we call “du foutage de gueule”. This is truly disappointing.”

Yeah I think that if their intention was for Imane to come across as supportive of Manon and Sofiane, they definitely failed at that as well. Imane never encouraged it, she did the opposite. She was jealous and tried to persuade Manon to not go out with him by giving her different excuses about why they wouldn’t work out.

That’s not encouraging/supportive lmaoo…. 🤨😂

I’m not sure what he was trying to convey because that’s definitely not what happened. at all. And I agree with the examples you wrote, especially with the apologies owed to Imane.

summary: the issue with og S4 was that Julie had so many ideas and wanted to please the whole fandom and she had writers block, and had...
body:
the issue with og S4 was that Julie had so many ideas and wanted to please the whole fandom and she had writers block, and had no idea what she was doing…and she really wanted william back so it all just went aåfufåråqwïweiråewapfsdsa. Like seriously…so many plots..so many storylines…so many plotholes..so many carrots..and for what?

the issue with skam france season 4 is that they love the drama way too much and took the storylines that made the least sense in the og and decided to keep those and add more drama to them. Another issue is that they filmed S3 & S4 back to back which imo made them focus more on developing S3 and crafting it, and not doing the same with S4. Because when you do a back to back season you don’t realize that the characters are changing..which made Emma way OOC at times, and the focus was more on the drama between Manon & Charles because they were building that up since S3 (and still made a mess out of it…). So instead of focusing on Imane in S3 and her new friendship with Lucas, and us seeing her drifting a bit from the squad and not always being in conversations etc…they had S3 and the characters be totally different so when S4 came..it felt weird. But mostly, they love their drama so yeah.
